{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σκοπ-ιά</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>σκοπ-ιή</b>, ἡ, <b>lookout-place</b>, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] especially a <b>hill-top</b>, σκοπιὴν εἰς παιπαλόεσσαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.97; ἀπὸ σκοπιῆς εἶδεν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.275, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.524; ἥμενος ἐν σκοπιῇ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.771 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὀπτῆρας δὲ κατὰ σκοπιὰς ὤτρυνα νέεσθαι each to his <b>lookout-place</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.261 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἄγγελος.. ἀπὸ τηλαυγέος φαινόμενος σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 550 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; <b>watch-tower</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.15; ὥσπερ ἀπὸ σ. μοι φαίνεται 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 445c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>peak, height</b>, of Cithaeron, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 130 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of Athos, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 237 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; Ἰλιὰς σ., of the Trojan acropolis, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 931 (Lyric poetry), compare “Ph.” 233 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 281 (Lyric poetry), etc.; Θάσου σκοπιαί “JHS” 29.93: _metaphorically_, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 9.47:—σκοπιαί personified as women (from Oreads), 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Philostrati majoris imagines” 2.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>look-out, watch</b>, σκοπιὴν ἔχειν to keep <b>watch</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homeru